newsitem.title: USA: U.S. bulk millfeeds - Prices steady to lower.
newsitem.headline: U.S. bulk millfeeds - Prices steady to lower.

text.p: U.S. millfeed prices were steady to lower on Tuesday as dealers noted continued featureless activity despite a gain in Chicago Board of Trade corn and soybean prices.
"We just do not see any trading interest going on," a Buffalo dealer said.

"Everybody is watching Chicago and saying look how strong it is, and nobody seems to be buying anything else. We find things pretty calm in the millfeed business as well as gluten feed and hominy feed."
One Kansas dealer noted that demand was down due to the spring-like weather.

"We are coming into that time of year where demand is not there," he said. "As it greens up across pastures in Oklahoma, Kansas and Texas, producers are turning out the livestock on grass and not feeding them any more."
Sellers are holding out so offerings are unchanged, a North Carolina dealer said. "The market is lackluster. The buyers, of course, are very quiet," he said.
